  <brief_title>Study of Talabostat and Rituximab in Advanced Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia (CLL)</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Point Therapeutics</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>FDA Office of Orphan Products Development</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this study is to assess the efficacy and safety of talabostat and rituximab
      in patients with advanced CLL who failed to respond, or have progressed following a prior
      response, to a fludarabine regimen.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
